My most vivid early memories are of the smell of fresh dug soil and the sharp clanking noise of metal tools on solid rock<br>
Looking up into the bearded face of my mother and father and seeing the pure joy and pride that they had in their first son. <br>
My father was a miner, indentured to Duppa Pickstone, the head of the Kaladim mining consortium. My mother worked as a servant for the Greybloom farming commune and was contracted concubine to King Kazon Stonehammer. They met each other one night after leaving the confines of Kaladim for a party at a mutual friend's, Kaila Rucksack. The party was long and the dwarven ale flowed like water and one time they awoke from a long night's festing in each others arms. After several other nitely ventures, they swore their love to each other. <br>
My father worked double shifts for a period, saving the extra money and hiding special crystals in his boots to help<br>
buy my mother's contract. But the king refused the purchase offer and forbade my mother from ever bringing up the subject again.<br>
However the king's primary wife saw how desperate my mother was to end her servitude to the king and one night she got the king drunk and placed the purchase agreement before him stating that it was a new law that would create more wealth through an increase in the tariffs charged for goods shipped in from other regions of Norrath. The following day my mother and father moved into an area of the mine reserved for workers families and several months later I was born.<br>
My father would work the mine by night and my mother continued her service to the commune until my father was able to save  the money to buy off her contract there as well. My mother then began working in the mines and they would take me with them to their work areas where I would play with rats that lived there and teeth on gems and crystals of various types. Soon my mother and father had made enough money to buy off my fathers contract and made plans to leave the city of Kaladim and join a group of pioneers. The group had contracted with a gnome exploration group to travel to the frozen wastes south of their homeland. Howevermy parents plans would never come to fruition. During my father's tenure as a miner he had made a couple of enemies who had connections with secret rogue faction that controlled specific areas within Northern Kaladim mines. Through their connections these enemies of my father informed on him and my mother to the king. And the king began to hatch a plan that would forever change the course of my life and the destiny of a kingdom.<br>
